  "text": "In the categorical task, [CITATION_1] found that the presence of semantic distractors led to target selection errors, but did not increase search times or modify the number or duration of fixations made on distractor words. In contrast, orthographic distractors slowed down search time because even though they no longer attracted participants' attention, participants needed more time to reject them than to reject neutral words. Hence, orthographic similarity between distractor words and the target influenced visual search even when participants did not known the target word in advance.",
